<!--
I feel like this is a good place for copious notes on how these projects are currently setup where they won't get deleted or forgotten.
This POM is an "aggregate" POM. It doesn't do the actual building of the project. Child "module" POMs inherit parts of this aggregate POM configuration.
 Builds are done in auto-sdk-java-parent module , and you need to make sure that project refers to all child projects as dependencies.
 shared-resources is just a resource dumping ground that gets pulled into the classpath for random things you want to be available everywhere.

There's some other kinda odd stuff, like the VERSION.txt file that the build module populates at build time so we can read our own version while running.
		hopefully you will never have to deal with these things


The flatten plugin below, and the weird stuff we're doing child module versions, is to follow this maven convention
https://maven.apache.org/maven-ci-friendly.html


It took me hours to get this all working together.... change at your peril
-->
